gnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. In nec mauris fringilla, sodales enim sed, auctor ligula. Ut pretium neque euismod mi imperdiet pharetra. Nulla arcu erat, consectetur quis ornare in, varius nec turpis. Praesent ligula nulla, placerat eleifend tincidunt id, vulputate in nunc. Curabitur id risus vehicula, varius eros sed, tempor mauris. Nunc luctus faucibus justo a eleifend. Maecenas sit amet turpis semper, molestie libero eget, egestas urna. Pellentesque quis luctus urna. Mauris elementum elit at congue viverra. Aenean tempus ipsum non arcu tincidunt consectetur.','Give','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2014-01-17 16:34:15','2014-01-17 16:34:15','',11,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/11-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(23,1,'2014-01-18 03:37:56','2014-01-18 03:37:56','<p dir=\"ltr\">Sister Eliza comes from a Christian Indian family in Goa.  She came to Mumbai to study Social Work.  She completed college and a M.A. degree in Social Work.  She was very much drawn to helping the abandoned and poor.  During this time, around 1990,  she was introduced to Sr. Paulette and became the first Sister to join the HMBT.  For more than 20 years now she has been a strong pillar to the order.  Today she spends most of her time running the day to day affairs of the Sahar Orphanage.  She also teaches at a nearby school and through this employment brings in financial support to run the orphanage.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://handmaids-local/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/nuns.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-22\" alt=\"nuns\" src=\"http://handmaids-local/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/nuns-225x300.png\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a>','Eliza','','publish','open','open','','eliza','','','2014-02-26 01:21:42','2014-02-26 01:21:42','',7,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/?page_id=23',1,'page','',0),(24,1,'2014-01-18 03:37:56','2014-01-18 03:37:56','This is a story about Eliza.','Eliza','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-01-18 03:37:56','2014-01-18 03:37:56','',23,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/23-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2014-01-18 03:38:36','2014-01-18 03:38:36','<p dir=\"ltr\">Sr. Paulette comes from a Christian Indian family from the island of Mauritus.  In her youth she decided to become a nun and came to Calcutta to join Mother Teresa.  For about 20 years she worked with Mother Teresa mainly helping women and children and doing family planning work.  She developed a severe back condition which required hospitalization. She was sent to a Mumbai hospital where she spent several months.  When she emerged from recuperation Mother Teresa urged her to remain in Mumbai in a life of service.  This is how, in 1989,  she became the foundress of a new order of nuns called the Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity.  Today the order contains about 40 nuns;  about 10 of these are directly working with Sr. Paulette at the orphanages.</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Paulette','','publish','open','open','','paulette','','','2014-02-26 01:20:21','2014-02-26 01:20:21','',7,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/?page_id=25',0,'page','',0),(26,1,'2014-01-18 03:38:36','2014-01-18 03:38:36','This is a story about Paulette.','Paulette','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision-v1','','','2014-01-18 03:38:36','2014-01-18 03:38:36','',25,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/25-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(70,1,'2014-02-15 19:52:37','2014-02-15 19:52:37','','classmates','','inherit','open','open','','classmates','','','2014-02-15 19:52:37','2014-02-15 19:52:37','',0,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/classmates.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(71,1,'2014-02-15 19:52:54','2014-02-15 19:52:54','','ready_to_learn','','inherit','open','open','','ready_to_learn','','','2014-02-15 19:52:54','2014-02-15 19:52:54','',0,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmai