\r\n\r\nSome of the kids are not \"orphans\" but have been brought by a parent or family member because they are physically or financially unable to care for them.  Often, there will be one surviving parent or a distant relative that continues to visit their child at the orphanages and this individual will eventually accept the child back.   But while they are there, the HMBT Sisters care for them completely.\r\n\r\nOn a typical day they will arise at 5:30-6:00 am.  After eating breakfast they will get dressed and ready for school which  goes till the early afternoon.   At Sahar the school is in the same building;  at Merces-Giriz the kids walk to nearby independent schools.   In the mid-afternoon there is additonal tutoring by a paid teacher at Sahar and by volunteer local college students at Merces-Giriz .  In the late afternoon the kids all do chores, have play time,  take baths, eat dinner and have prayer time.  They typically go to bed around 9 pm.    On Sundays, there is extra time for watching T.V.,  having a party, music, dance,  and also visits by family members or persons from the community.\r\n\r\nOn this page you will find some profiles typical of the orphans.','Orphans','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 14:15:18','2014-02-26 14:15:18','',151,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/151-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(193,1,'2014-02-26 14:21:08','2014-02-26 14:21:08','Preeti was born in April 2000.  She has been living at Merces Orphanage since the age of 5.   Her dad died of tuberculosis just before.   Her mother brought her to the orphange because she couldn\'t take care of her.  In 2013 her mother also died of tuberculosis.   Preeti has been treated and cured.\n\nPreeti is first in her class of 47 students at nearby St. Thomas High School where she takes Geography,  English,  History, Science, Math, Drawing and a computer class.  Her favorite subject is English.  She hopes to become a teacher someday.  She is very happy to be living at this orphanage and is greatful to the sisters for looking after her.','Preeti Kutade','','inherit','open','open','','154-autosave-v1','','','2014-02-26 14:21:08','2014-02-26 14:21:08','',154,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/154-autosave-v1',0,'revision','',0),(194,1,'2014-02-26 14:21:20','2014-02-26 14:21:20','Preeti was born in April 2000.  She has been living at Merces Orphanage since the age of 5.   Her dad died of tuberculosis just before.   Her mother brought her to the orphange because she couldn\'t take care of her.  In 2013 her mother also died of tuberculosis.   Preeti has been treated and cured.\r\n\r\nPreeti is first in her class of 47 students at nearby St. Thomas High School where she takes Geography,  English,  History, Science, Math, Drawing and a computer class.  Her favorite subject is English.  She hopes to become a teacher someday.  She is very happy to be living at this orphanage and is greatful to the sisters for looking after her.','Preeti Kutade','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-v1','','','2014-02-26 14:21:20','2014-02-26 14:21:20','',154,'http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/uncategorized/154-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(195,1,'2014-02-26 14:23:17','2014-02-26 14:23:17','<p dir=\"ltr\">The Handmaids Orphanages were started by an order of nuns known as the Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity.   The main mission of the HMBT order was to reach out to impoverished women and children for their health and well being.  In the early years starting around 1989, it was only Srs. Paulette and Eliza.  Together they  worked and lived in the slum areas around the International Airport in Mumbai known as the Sahar Slums (the specific location of the current Sahar Orphanage is called Church Pakadi).</p>\r\n Living and working in the slums they were aware of the serious problems faced by families, especially women and children: lack of food, severe malnutrition, lack of 